{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb67c6681-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300aa–27"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"300aa–27"},"text":"§ 300aa–27.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Mandate for safer childhood vaccines","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb67c6682-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300aa–27/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" General rule","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In the administration of this part and other pertinent laws under the jurisdiction of the Secretary, the Secretary shall—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb67c6683-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300aa–27/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" promote the development of childhood vaccines that result in fewer and less serious adverse reactions than those vaccines on the market on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-12-22"},"text":"December 22, 1987","children":[],"tail":", and promote the refinement of such vaccines, and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb67c6684-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300aa–27/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" make or assure improvements in, and otherwise use the authorities of the Secretary with respect to, the licensing, manufacturing, processing, testing, labeling, warning, use instructions, distribution, storage, administration, field surveillance, adverse reaction reporting, and recall of reactogenic lots or batches, of vaccines, and research on vaccines, in order to reduce the risks of adverse reactions to vaccines.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb67c6685-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300aa–27/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Task force","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb67c6686-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300aa–27/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary shall establish a task force on safer childhood vaccines which shall consist of the Director of the National Institutes of Health, the Commissioner of the Food and Drug Administration, and the Director of the Centers for Disease Control.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb67c6687-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300aa–27/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Director of the National Institutes of Health shall serve as chairman of the task force.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb67c6688-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300aa–27/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In consultation with the Advisory Commission on Childhood Vaccines, the task force shall prepare recommendations to the Secretary concerning implementation of the requirements of subsection (a).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb67c6689-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s300aa–27/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Report","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Within 2 years after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-12-22"},"text":"December 22, 1987","children":[],"tail":", and periodically thereafter, the Secretary shall prepare and transmit to the Committee on Energy and Commerce of the House of Representatives and the Committee on Labor and Human Resources of the Senate a report describing the actions taken pursuant to subsection (a) during the preceding 2-year period."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb67c668a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373"},"text":"July 1, 1944, ch. 373","children":[],"tail":", title XXI, § 2127, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/660/tIII/s311/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–660, title III, § 311(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-11-14"},"text":"Nov. 14, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3777"},"text":"100 Stat. 3777","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/203/tIV/s4302/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–203, title IV, § 4302(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/1330-221"},"text":"101 Stat. 1330–221","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/239/tVI/s6601/q"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–239, title VI, § 6601(q)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/2292"},"text":"103 Stat. 2292","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb67c668b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb67c668c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idb67c668d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsecs. (a)(1), (c), “","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-12-22"},"text":"December 22, 1987","children":[],"tail":"” substituted for “the effective date of this subpart” on authority of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/660/s323"},"text":"section 323 of Pub. L. 99–660","children":[],"tail":", as amended, set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s300aa–1"},"text":"section 300aa–1 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb67c668e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—Subsecs. (b), (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/239"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–239","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (b) and redesignated former subsec. (b) as (c)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1987—Subsecs. (a)(1), (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/203"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–203","children":[],"tail":" substituted “effective date of this subpart” for “effective date of this part”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb67c668f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"idb67c6690-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Committee on Labor and Human Resources of Senate changed to Committee on Health, Education, Labor, and Pensions of Senate by Senate Resolution No. 20, One Hundred Sixth Congress, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-01-19"},"text":"Jan. 19, 1999","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Committee on Energy and Commerce of House of Representatives treated as referring to Committee on Commerce of House of Representatives by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/14/s1/a"},"text":"section 1(a) of Pub. L. 104–14","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s21"},"text":"section 21 of Title 2","children":[],"tail":", The Congress. Committee on Commerce of House of Representatives changed to Committee on Energy and Commerce of House of Representatives, and jurisdiction over matters relating to securities and exchanges and insurance generally transferred to Committee on Financial Services of House of Representatives by House Resolution No. 5, One Hundred Seventh Congress, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-01-03"},"text":"Jan. 3, 2001","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Centers for Disease Control changed to Centers for Disease Control and Prevention by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/531/tIII/s312"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–531, title III, § 312","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-27"},"text":"Oct. 27, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"